         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">Botanic Garden ¶ Melbourne, 19th April 1873 ¶ Sir ¶  ¶ In accordance with your kind promise already orally given, I have the honor to solicit, that you will be pleased to sanction the transfer of the ...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">73.04.19a</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">To James Casey</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">J73/7112, unit 750, VPRS 44/P inward registered and unregistered correspondence, VA 538 Department of Crown Lands and Survey, Public Record Office, Victoria.<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; "/>
            </p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn0" n="1">
                  <p rend="FootnoteText"
                     style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>MS written by Georg Luehmann and signed by M.</p>
               </note>Botanic Garden</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">Melbourne, 19th April 1873</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Sir</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>In accordance with your kind promise already orally given, I have the honor to solicit, that you will be pleased to sanction the transfer of the sum of £110.- .- from the vote for 'Purchase of Plants and Publication of Works' to the vote for 'Stores, Forage etc.<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn1" n="2">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>There is no closing quotation mark.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>also the transfer of the sum of £120.-<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>voted for a<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>'Test plantation in the Ranges'<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>and of<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>£74.10/—, surplus of vote for 'Reward to orphanboys employed in the Garden,'<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>making in the aggregate £194.10/— to the vote for 'Wages', in order to enable me to meet the necessary expenditure during the current financial year. The vote for Transit and Incidental Expenses will also be insufficient, especially in consequence of the unexpected charge for packing of Ferntrees for Holland;<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn2" n="3">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>See<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>M to J. Casey. 27 February 1873 (in this edition as 73-02-27a), and subsequernt correspondence.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>I have therefore the honor to solicit that you will also grant a transfer of the sum of £30.- .-<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>to this vote from the vote for 'Purchase of<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Plants &amp; Publication of Works.'</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">I have the honor to be</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Sir</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Your very obedient servant</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ferd. von Mueller,</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Director Botanic Garden</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">The Honorable the Commissioner of Lands &amp; Survey<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn3" n="4">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Casey approved M's requests on 24 April 1873. The transfers were completed and M was duly informed on 19 May. On 21 May, M 'Returned with best thanks to Mr Agg' the relevant file.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
            </p>
         </div>
      </body>
